&lt;li&gt;Ensuring RFI procedures are followed and as built drawings are accurately completed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain documentation of inspections, punch lists, and quality checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforce safety standards and proper lockout/tagout procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring proper handoff documentation is prepared and available for the commissioning team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active &lt;strong&gt;Master Electrician license&lt;/strong&gt; (or equivalent state certification)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8–15+ years of commercial or industrial electrical experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of medium- and low-voltage power distribution, UPS systems, generators, switchgear, and critical power infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
